The pexforfun thing seemed pretty clever:<p><pre><code>  // What values of v and i can cause an exception? Ask Pex to find out!
  public static void Puzzle(int[] v, int i)
  {
    if (v[i + 2] + 5 == v.Length + i)
      throw new Exception("hidden bug!"); 
  }
</code></pre>
and then it automatically finds the breaking input:<p><pre><code>  {-6} 	 -2 	 Exception 	 hidden bug!</code></pre>
